# CODEOWNERS — Golden Path HITL review routing (template).
#
# Combined with the `main` ruleset (governance/rulesets/main.json), which sets
# require_code_owner_review + 1 required approval + thread resolution, this is
# the human-in-the-loop gate: agents (acting as their own GitHub App identities)
# can open and prepare PRs, but a human owner must approve before merge. Agent
# apps are deliberately NOT repo admins, so they cannot bypass these rules.
#
# Replace @OWNER with your repo's owning team (e.g. @three-cubes/maintainers) or
# user before committing. Keep the gate-critical paths owner-only — they must
# never be self-approved by an agent.

# Default owner — every change requires the owner's review.
*                            @OWNER

# Gate-critical: CI, automation, and the rules themselves. An agent must never
# be able to weaken the gates that enforce HITL.
/.github/                    @OWNER
/CODEOWNERS                  @OWNER
/.github/CODEOWNERS          @OWNER
